Being fit/in shape isn’t just about looking good in the mirror. 

There are SO many more benefits than just the physical appearance. 

It’s the self love you gain. 

It’s the confidence you gain. 

It’s the discipline you learn. 

It’s the habits you form.

It’s being able to get through a day without the aches and pains of being overweight. 

It’s becoming healthier and being able to keep up with your kids when they ask to go play ball. 

It’s being able to be around for when you have grandkids. 

It’s being able to take your dog to the dog park without getting winded. 

It’s having that confidence to ask that girl out. 

Some of us may start our fitness journey for the aesthetics/ looks not realizing the greater impact that it will have on our quality of life. 

Stop disrespecting yourself. You’ve got one chance at this thing called life. If you’re tired of being tired this is your sign. Let’s elevate your life!! 

DM me “IM NEXT” if you’re ready to start living the life that you deserve💪

9:
“I’ll do it later…”

-Is one of the worst mindsets you can have.

I fall victim to this as well. Over the last few days I have been working out a little earlier than normal. I eat my pre workout meal then go to the gym first thing. I’ve been telling myself, I’ll go to the gym and do my morning routine later. Guess what’s happened over the last few days?

I haven’t done my morning routine of affirmation, reading and goal setting.

It’s so easy to put it off until a more convenient time. I get it, I really do. 

However, having that mindset will get you nowhere. More often than not you won’t do the task later. 

Now relate that to fitness.

How many of you have told yourself “I’ll go to the gym later” for the last year? Are you happy with the results you’ve gotten from the work you haven’t done? 

Exactly. I’m guessing not. So I challenge you to go to the gym today. Get home from work,  change and leave. Don’t sit down. Don’t say you’ll go later. Bc you won’t. 

Don’t know what to do in the gym? 
Don’t know what to eat to get results? 
Need someone to hold you accountable? 

Hi, my names Dalton. Hmu, I got you🤝

-Coach Dalton
